{
  "stem": "26699.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were behind the iron curtain, which was impossible to cross it, to go to the Western Europe.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in the autumn of 1958, a year after graduation, while I was working on one of the construction sites in Bucharest, all of a sudden-- I can't explain what happened-- it was accepted that the Jews can apply for leaving the country to go to Israel.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So Romania had a large Jewish population, even after the war, after the program and other things which happened.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Apparently, before the war, the Romanian population exceeded half a million-- Jewish population exceeded half a million people.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "After the war, probably, they were left 253,000 people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And one of the main centers was Bucharest.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So after this rumor spread that Jews can apply for passports to go to Israel, long queues in the front of the main police station of Bucharest of Jews started to take place.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were standing in the queue for day and night.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I, my father, and my mother, we standed on this queue for two days and a night to get the forms for application for us to immigrate to Israel.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And sometimes, when so many Jews were standing in a queue-- there were still this iron guard people alive around.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I heard some comments from them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Said, what a good job a machine gun would have done with this queue, having probably the memories of what happened at Iasi.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we applied in 1958.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The immediate result was that I was declared enemy of the regime, together with my father, of course.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was thrown out from the youth organization of Communist Party, of course.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I had to return my membership card in a not so pleasant meeting where people spoke against my betrayal.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
